1. show databases -> list all available databases
2. db -> current databases you are in
3. use database_name -> you are in this database_name
4. show collections -> list collections of database you are using
5. db.dropDatabase() -> drops database
6. db.createCollection(‘collectionName’) -> creates collection
7. db.collectionName.drop() -> drops the collection
8. db.collectionName.insert({}) -> inserting collection 
9. db.collectionName.insertMany([{}, {}, {}]) -> inserting multiple rows
10. db.collectionName.find() -> lists all rows
11. db.collectionName.find().pretty() -> lists all rows nicely
12. db.collectionName.find({key: ‘value’}).pretty() -> lists rows with specific key-value pair nicely
13. db.collectionName.find().pretty().limit(number) -> lists limited(number specified) rows nicely
14. db.collectionName.find({}).count() -> counts number of rows in collection
15. db.collectionName.find().sort({___:1}) -> sorts in ascending(1) or descending order(-1)
16. db.collectionName.findOne({__:__}) -> finds the first row item matching the object
17. db.collectionName.update({filter}, {change}) -> updating the row
18. db.collectionName.update({filter}, {change}, {upsert: true}) -> updating-add the row if not present
19. 
